Description
-----------

The **mirrorRenderMap** keyword defines a buffer in which a reflection
is rendered into.

Usage
-----

    mirrorRenderMap

Parameters
----------

-   [width] = The width of the buffer in pixels
-   [height] = The height of the buffer in pixels

Example
-------

Renders a map with a dimension of 128 by 128...

    {
       mirrorRenderMap   128 128
    }

Notes
-----

The results produced by this keyword often times require some
manipulation via the
[translate](Translate_%28Material_stage_keyword%29 "Translate (Material stage keyword)")
and
[scale](Scale_%28Material_stage_keyword%29 "Scale (Material stage keyword)")
keywords in order to be useful.

